div.p:
The versified selections are as follows: Ruskinʼs book 1 begins with the latter half of Scottʼs chap. 5, 
                        the Sacristanʼs failure to gain passage over the drawbridge and, in fording the Tweed on horseback, his encounter with the White Lady; 
                        and book 1 ends by briefly summarizing portions of Scottʼs chap. 7, the Abbot and Father Eustaceʼs resolve on hearing the Sacristanʼs adventure.
